WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:15.015
[dramatic music playing]

3
00:00:41.917 --> 00:00:44.419
[mysterious music playing]

4
00:00:50.509 --> 00:00:54.096
[unsettling music playing]

5
00:01:17.077 --> 00:01:19.496
[flies buzzing]

6
00:01:33.218 --> 00:01:34.303
[sighs]

7
00:01:35.137 --> 00:01:36.305
Fuck.

8
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:41.977
[intense. ominous music playing]

9
00:01:54.990 --> 00:01:57.326
[dogs barking]

10
00:02:10.839 --> 00:02:11.840
Hey.

11
00:02:13.967 --> 00:02:15.511
I'm looking for Robert Cady.

12
00:02:16.345 --> 00:02:17.346
[sighs]

13
00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:24.645
- Am I in the right place?
- Oh. sure. ma'am. [chuckles]

14
00:02:25.395 --> 00:02:26.813
Follow me. [chuckles]

15
00:02:39.117 --> 00:02:40.452
That's him right there.

16
00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:42.496
[blows]

17
00:02:47.543 --> 00:02:48.919
Max's lady lawyer.

18
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:56.134
Let me guess. You were
in the neighborhood and got a little lost?

19
00:02:57.594 --> 00:02:58.804
I'm looking for Crystal.

20
00:02:58.887 --> 00:03:00.556
[unsettling music playing]

21
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:04.476
- Oh?
- Yeah.

22
00:03:09.314 --> 00:03:10.399
Are you now?

23
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:13.193
Yeah.

24
00:03:13.777 --> 00:03:15.153
[Hester] Who's that?

25
00:03:15.821 --> 00:03:17.614
Little Anna Deveraux. Mama.

26
00:03:19.032 --> 00:03:20.784
- What's she doing here?
- Mm-hmm.

27
00:03:20.868 --> 00:03:22.578
Do they know about Crystal?

28
00:03:22.661 --> 00:03:23.829
[Robert] Now. now. now.

29
00:03:24.663 --> 00:03:26.248
Don't get your panties twisted.

30
00:03:26.874 --> 00:03:28.792
Nothing burning here but the daylight.

31
00:03:31.503 --> 00:03:32.504
Here's Crystal.

32
00:03:32.588 --> 00:03:35.883
Aw. there's my baby.

33
00:03:35.966 --> 00:03:37.384
Yeah.

34
00:03:37.467 --> 00:03:39.303
Here you go. my lovey.

35
00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:41.805
Yeah. good job.

36
00:03:42.472 --> 00:03:43.765
Mmm. Uh-huh.

37
00:03:44.266 --> 00:03:47.853
Look. if you just tell me where I can
find her. then I'll be on my way.

38
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:49.605
You leave Crystal be.

39
00:03:51.190 --> 00:03:54.651
Took that girl half her life
to get her demons on a leash.

40
00:03:54.735 --> 00:03:57.863
I swear to God.
I will make you sorry you agitate her.

41
00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.740
[menacing music playing]

42
00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:02.868
You best be on your way. ma'am.

43
00:04:09.625 --> 00:04:10.626
Okay.

44
00:04:16.964 --> 00:04:19.301
It's all right.
It's all right. it's all right.

45
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:30.062
Got nothing for you here.

46
00:04:37.528 --> 00:04:40.197
[eerie music playing]

47
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:56.338
Just a few more things to do...

48
00:04:58.382 --> 00:05:01.468
and then I will join you.

49
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:12.437
[intense. ominous music playing]

50
00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:26.034
["Waitin' for the Bus" playing]

51
00:05:26.118 --> 00:05:27.452
[Anna] <i>You know this girl?</i>

52
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.539
- Crystal Cady.
- [bartender] Nope.

53
00:05:31.790 --> 00:05:33.333
You know the family though. right?

54
00:05:33.417 --> 00:05:35.169
They live just down the road.

55
00:05:37.004 --> 00:05:39.089
You a paying customer or not?

56
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:48.390
Well. devil's already in the door.

57
00:05:49.641 --> 00:05:51.643
Whiskey. Make it neat. [sighs]

58
00:06:10.454 --> 00:06:11.580
[music stops]

59
00:06:22.674 --> 00:06:23.926
[inhales sharply]

60
00:06:27.471 --> 00:06:29.389
[patrons chattering]

61
00:06:46.156 --> 00:06:47.491
Hey. sunshine.

62
00:06:48.617 --> 00:06:50.494
I heard you were looking for me.

63
00:06:50.577 --> 00:06:53.163
[sinister music playing]

64
00:06:55.874 --> 00:06:57.209
Oh. fuck.

65
00:07:34.538 --> 00:07:35.664
Hello?

66
00:07:36.498 --> 00:07:37.499
Hey. bud.

67
00:07:41.128 --> 00:07:42.129
Hey.

68
00:07:43.714 --> 00:07:46.800
Uh. Zack?

69
00:07:47.885 --> 00:07:49.136
<i>Is that you?</i>

70
00:07:50.137 --> 00:07:51.138
Yeah. it's me.

71
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:52.848
[sighs]

72
00:07:53.390 --> 00:07:54.391
[chuckles]

73
00:07:55.851 --> 00:07:56.935
Well. how you doing?

74
00:07:58.437 --> 00:07:59.438
[Zack] <i>I'm okay.</i>

75
00:08:00.314 --> 00:08:03.108
<i>How... How are you guys?</i>

76
00:08:04.026 --> 00:08:07.237
Uh. you know. taking it day by day.

77
00:08:08.447 --> 00:08:09.865
<i>We miss you.</i>

78
00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:12.367
I wanna come home.

79
00:08:12.451 --> 00:08:14.119
[ominous music playing]

80
00:08:14.953 --> 00:08:16.788
I know. bud. You will.

81
00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:18.498
<i>Soon.</i>

82
00:08:21.168 --> 00:08:23.337
<i>Just hang in there a little while longer.</i>

83
00:08:23.921 --> 00:08:25.881
Then we'll all be home together.

84
00:08:28.592 --> 00:08:31.011
Hey. Group's starting.

85
00:08:32.888 --> 00:08:34.765
- I gotta go.
- <i>Zack...</i>

86
00:08:51.406 --> 00:08:52.783
[inmate 1] Give me your biscuit.

87
00:08:55.744 --> 00:08:57.829
- What?
- You ain't gonna eat it.

88
00:08:58.664 --> 00:08:59.748
Give it to me.

89
00:09:01.834 --> 00:09:02.835
I might.

90
00:09:03.335 --> 00:09:04.336
[inmate 1] Really?

91
00:09:07.548 --> 00:09:09.216
I think you're too afraid to eat.

92
00:09:10.592 --> 00:09:12.594
Everyone in here knows
that she's gonna fuck you up.

93
00:09:12.678 --> 00:09:14.221
[ominous music playing]

94
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:15.556
But she's making you wait

95
00:09:16.139 --> 00:09:20.352
so that me and everyone in here
can get a piece of you first.

96
00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:23.313
Now give me the fucking biscuit.

97
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:29.653
Fuck you.

98
00:09:30.153 --> 00:09:32.656
- [sinister. tense music playing]
- [both grunting]

99
00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:35.158
- [inmate 2] Holy fuck.
- [inmate 3] Get her bitch ass!

100
00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:37.619
[inmate 4 shouting indistinctly]

101
00:09:37.703 --> 00:09:39.538
[inmate 5] Little white girl!

102
00:09:41.373 --> 00:09:43.292
- [Nevaeh shrieks]
- [inmates groan]

103
00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:45.627
[panting]

104
00:09:47.546 --> 00:09:50.340
- [grunting. whimpering]
- [inmate 6] Oh. shit!

105
00:09:50.424 --> 00:09:51.592
- [door lock buzzes]
- She's mine.

106
00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:53.302
[officer] Shit! Shut up.

107
00:09:53.385 --> 00:09:55.137
Goddamn it.

108
00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:56.555
Get down. All right.

109
00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:58.682
[chuckles]

110
00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:01.518
[breathing shakily]

111
00:10:20.162 --> 00:10:22.998
Shit. [breathing shakily]

112
00:10:32.841 --> 00:10:36.512
- [breathing heavily] Hey.
- [recording tone plays]

113
00:10:37.721 --> 00:10:39.097
Um. Noa. I'm fine.

114
00:10:39.181 --> 00:10:42.893
[stammers] I'm. um...
Look. I know this sounds insane.

115
00:10:42.976 --> 00:10:44.770
- but I'm with Crystal Cady...
- [shuffling]

116
00:10:44.853 --> 00:10:47.439
...and I need you to dig up
everything you can on her.

117
00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:49.399
I'll do the same.

118
00:10:50.901 --> 00:10:54.821
Will you tell Tom
that I'm gonna make this right?

119
00:10:54.905 --> 00:10:57.324
- Okay? [breathing heavily]
- [message sent tone plays]

120
00:11:08.210 --> 00:11:11.755
- [glass clinking]
- [breathing shakily]

121
00:11:13.924 --> 00:11:15.968
Okay. [inhales sharply]

122
00:11:16.802 --> 00:11:18.136
[breathing shakily]

123
00:11:34.069 --> 00:11:36.363
[Crystal] Well. good morning. princess.

124
00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:40.742
Morning.

125
00:11:40.826 --> 00:11:44.371
I hope my humble abode
was up to your standards.

126
00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:46.290
I survived.

127
00:11:48.834 --> 00:11:49.835
You want a beer?

128
00:11:52.796 --> 00:11:53.922
Thanks.

129
00:11:57.843 --> 00:11:58.844
[Crystal chuckles]

130
00:11:59.761 --> 00:12:02.973
What. did you learn that
from your sorority sisters?

131
00:12:06.602 --> 00:12:10.439
Well. who's to say they taught me?
Maybe I taught them.

132
00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:16.528
Maybe I taught their boyfriends
and boyfriends taught them.

133
00:12:16.612 --> 00:12:18.697
- You're mouthy.
- Mmm.

134
00:12:20.824 --> 00:12:21.992
Where's my gun?

135
00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:25.037
Safekeeping.

136
00:12:29.541 --> 00:12:30.542
So...

137
00:12:32.085 --> 00:12:33.754
tell me about you and Max.

138
00:12:38.050 --> 00:12:39.051
You first.

139
00:12:39.635 --> 00:12:42.179
[ominous music playing]

140
00:12:42.846 --> 00:12:45.349
[officer] Bowden. you got a visitor.

141
00:12:56.151 --> 00:12:57.611
[breathes shakily]

142
00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:16.338
Wow. It's very impressive.
the way you look.

143
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:17.422
[chuckles]

144
00:13:17.965 --> 00:13:20.425
Hey. are you making any friends here?

145
00:13:20.509 --> 00:13:21.885
I worry about you.

146
00:13:21.969 --> 00:13:25.681
How do your... your fellow inmates
feel about prosecutors?

147
00:13:25.764 --> 00:13:28.517
They're... They're tricky with that. no?

148
00:13:28.600 --> 00:13:29.768
They don't know yet?

149
00:13:29.852 --> 00:13:31.144
Wow. They don't know yet.

150
00:13:31.228 --> 00:13:34.106
Well. it won't be long
until they find out.

151
00:13:34.189 --> 00:13:36.108
Are you just here
to run your fucking mouth. man.

152
00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:39.820
or do you have anything worthwhile
to say to me?

153
00:13:39.903 --> 00:13:40.904
Yes. actually.

154
00:13:40.988 --> 00:13:43.198
Well. I want to tell you something
that is very important.

155
00:13:43.282 --> 00:13:48.537
Make sure you save
all the Kikkoman soy sauce packages

156
00:13:48.620 --> 00:13:50.289
- from the commissary.
- [laughing]

157
00:13:50.372 --> 00:13:53.083
Because then you mix
the soy sauce with the mayo

158
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:54.585
and you can create this sauce

159
00:13:54.668 --> 00:13:57.421
- that'll really fix the most bland meal.
- Fuck you.

160
00:13:57.504 --> 00:13:58.922
- [knocks on glass]
- Hey!

161
00:13:59.006 --> 00:14:01.592
[laughing] It's true though.

162
00:14:01.675 --> 00:14:02.676
Sorry. sorry.

163
00:14:03.260 --> 00:14:05.470
You're gonna wanna hear this.

164
00:14:12.686 --> 00:14:14.897
[blows] How does it feel?

165
00:14:14.980 --> 00:14:16.607
How does it feel. Tom?

166
00:14:18.025 --> 00:14:19.026
Being in there.

167
00:14:21.111 --> 00:14:26.116
You need permission
to go and eat or sleep or take a shit.

168
00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:27.951
You need permission for everything.

169
00:14:28.035 --> 00:14:29.453
[sinister music playing]

170
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:35.501
How are you feeling
with the experience of losing. totally.

171
00:14:35.584 --> 00:14:39.379
the control and the will
of doing what you want when you need?

172
00:14:39.463 --> 00:14:41.298
You don't have that in there. right?

173
00:14:42.174 --> 00:14:43.175
It's hard.

174
00:14:45.177 --> 00:14:51.225
But I'm giving you the possibility
to become the man your family needs.

175
00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:57.189
One of my friends is going to send you
a gift to your cell. Today.

176
00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:58.941
So... [inhales deeply]

177
00:15:00.234 --> 00:15:01.401
...a gift.

178
00:15:01.485 --> 00:15:02.486
In your cell.

179
00:15:04.571 --> 00:15:05.989
It will be your salvation.

180
00:15:17.125 --> 00:15:19.586
[Crystal] Sounds like
he did a real number on you.

181
00:15:21.255 --> 00:15:23.799
Fucked up your whole life.

182
00:15:24.383 --> 00:15:25.926
Fucked up your family.

183
00:15:26.969 --> 00:15:28.011
That's Max.

184
00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:30.806
That's gotta sting.

185
00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:35.561
but I guess you were really into him. huh?

186
00:15:37.271 --> 00:15:39.022
No. No. course not.

187
00:15:39.106 --> 00:15:40.732
I told you. what you saw...

188
00:15:40.816 --> 00:15:41.900
He kissed me...

189
00:15:41.984 --> 00:15:43.277
Against your will.

190
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:44.528
Yes. against my will.

191
00:15:45.112 --> 00:15:47.239
[chuckling] But you sure looked willing.

192
00:15:48.031 --> 00:15:49.324
What about you?

193
00:15:49.908 --> 00:15:53.745
Why are you following him around?
Stalking him. taking pictures.

194
00:15:54.329 --> 00:15:56.498
Seems to me
like you're the one infatuated.

195
00:15:57.249 --> 00:15:59.543
- Oh. I'm not infatuated.
- Mmm.

196
00:15:59.626 --> 00:16:01.920
It's because I know Max Cady

197
00:16:02.004 --> 00:16:04.131
and I know what he's up to.

198
00:16:04.214 --> 00:16:05.716
That's why I have those pictures.

199
00:16:05.799 --> 00:16:09.845
because as long as he knows that
I have pictures of him doing bad stuff.

200
00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:11.513
then he won't come after me.

201
00:16:12.014 --> 00:16:15.100
And no. you cannot see them
because they're mine.

202
00:16:17.144 --> 00:16:18.145
What about Amy?

203
00:16:19.479 --> 00:16:20.480
And Melissa?

204
00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:22.566
What did he do to them?

205
00:16:22.649 --> 00:16:27.613
I'm just saying that when Max
wants to make something happen.

206
00:16:28.322 --> 00:16:29.698
he just makes it happen.

207
00:16:30.657 --> 00:16:33.035
He'll make people do anything he wants.

208
00:16:34.161 --> 00:16:35.162
Anything. like...

209
00:16:36.747 --> 00:16:38.040
kill themselves?

210
00:16:39.541 --> 00:16:42.252
Amy Brancato. she had moved to Asheville.

211
00:16:42.753 --> 00:16:43.962
She got a new man.

212
00:16:44.046 --> 00:16:46.089
she was getting her life back together

213
00:16:46.173 --> 00:16:48.926
and then Max comes calling
and that's all it took.

214
00:16:49.009 --> 00:16:52.262
She came here and she started
living with her stepmom again.

215
00:16:52.346 --> 00:16:54.681
And that's where she was
when they found her.

216
00:16:57.392 --> 00:16:58.519
What else do you know?

217
00:17:06.068 --> 00:17:07.069
[sniffs]

218
00:17:30.551 --> 00:17:33.512
[line ringing]

219
00:17:34.221 --> 00:17:35.222
Hey.

220
00:17:36.139 --> 00:17:37.558
[Nevaeh] <i>I gave her a taste.</i>

221
00:17:38.684 --> 00:17:40.394
<i>She knows I'm gonna make her life hell.</i>

222
00:17:40.477 --> 00:17:42.062
I'm so lucky to have you.

223
00:17:42.145 --> 00:17:43.856
[chuckles] My little girl.

224
00:17:45.607 --> 00:17:47.025
I could help more. you know.

225
00:17:48.151 --> 00:17:50.612
Um. if I was with you.

226
00:17:51.530 --> 00:17:53.532
<i>Have you figured out how to get me out?</i>

227
00:17:53.615 --> 00:17:56.493
Nevaeh. you are my eyes and my ears.
and I need you.

228
00:17:56.577 --> 00:17:58.787
- I can't get you out yet.
- [unsettling music playing]

229
00:17:58.871 --> 00:18:01.123
- You said it would be soon.
- <i>And it will be.</i>

230
00:18:01.206 --> 00:18:03.500
<i>I just need one more thing.</i>

231
00:18:03.584 --> 00:18:09.089
I need you to find out
from Natalie where her mother is.

232
00:18:10.549 --> 00:18:11.758
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

233
00:18:12.718 --> 00:18:13.719
Yeah.

234
00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:14.803
<i>Good.</i>

235
00:18:14.887 --> 00:18:15.888
Great.

236
00:18:17.139 --> 00:18:18.140
And then...

237
00:18:19.349 --> 00:18:20.475
[whispers] ...finish it.

238
00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:23.520
Like. kill Natalie?

239
00:18:25.397 --> 00:18:26.398
Like. for sure?

240
00:18:26.481 --> 00:18:28.192
Before Anna dies.

241
00:18:28.984 --> 00:18:31.320
I need her to feel the pain of...

242
00:18:32.988 --> 00:18:33.989
losing a child.

243
00:18:35.866 --> 00:18:36.867
Just like I did.

244
00:18:38.327 --> 00:18:39.661
I need her to feel that.

245
00:18:40.704 --> 00:18:42.122
<i>Think of what she did to me.</i>

246
00:18:42.789 --> 00:18:44.041
of what she did to you.

247
00:18:44.791 --> 00:18:47.127
Sixteen years we could have been together.

248
00:18:47.211 --> 00:18:48.212
Father and daughter.

249
00:18:49.129 --> 00:18:50.714
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

250
00:18:50.797 --> 00:18:53.467
<i>And I'll be so proud of you.</i>

251
00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:54.927
And then you'll get me out...

252
00:18:55.010 --> 00:18:57.012
[breathing shakily] ...right?

253
00:19:00.766 --> 00:19:02.392
Right? [panting]

254
00:19:02.476 --> 00:19:03.477
Dad?

255
00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:05.687
<i>Daddy?</i> [panting continues]

256
00:19:08.440 --> 00:19:09.525
Yes.

257
00:19:09.608 --> 00:19:11.944
I love you so much.

258
00:19:12.528 --> 00:19:15.239
<i>Bye. I love you.</i>

259
00:19:15.322 --> 00:19:16.490
Bye.

260
00:19:16.990 --> 00:19:19.284
[breathing heavily]

261
00:19:23.497 --> 00:19:25.999
[ominous music playing]

262
00:19:35.968 --> 00:19:37.719
Why'd you stop that girl
from attacking me?

263
00:19:37.803 --> 00:19:41.932
Same reason I save tuna pouches
from commissary. To eat later.

264
00:19:42.015 --> 00:19:43.016
Don't do that.

265
00:19:44.810 --> 00:19:46.061
You opened up to me.

266
00:19:46.144 --> 00:19:47.521
We both know that was real.

267
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:49.189
It's called acting. babe.

268
00:19:50.440 --> 00:19:52.150
Or did you forget
I was fucking your brother?

269
00:20:03.537 --> 00:20:07.291
[Crystal] Amy's stepmom.
Brenda. is a real hoot.

270
00:20:07.374 --> 00:20:12.296
She had a pet raccoon for a while
until one of the neighbors ran it over.

271
00:20:13.964 --> 00:20:16.300
Jesus Christ.
Have you ever driven a car before?

272
00:20:16.383 --> 00:20:17.634
Oh. well. that's nothing.

273
00:20:17.718 --> 00:20:22.931
One time. I did 16 donuts
in a Piggly Wiggly with a blindfold on.

274
00:20:23.432 --> 00:20:24.433
It was a dare.

275
00:20:24.516 --> 00:20:28.020
I'd had. like. a 12-pack.
but I... I'd do it anyway.

276
00:20:28.103 --> 00:20:30.355
[mysterious music playing]

277
00:20:30.439 --> 00:20:32.232
So this is the house.

278
00:20:33.317 --> 00:20:35.527
Hopefully Brenda's home.

279
00:20:42.868 --> 00:20:45.078
[Anna] How'd you get that scar?
On your face.

280
00:20:45.162 --> 00:20:48.373
Oh. I was escaping from the clinic

281
00:20:48.457 --> 00:20:50.918
and I got in a fight with a windowpane.

282
00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:52.711
Seriously?

283
00:20:52.794 --> 00:20:56.048
Oh. yeah. They fight dirty. [chuckles]

284
00:20:56.131 --> 00:20:57.799
One time. I dated a guard.

285
00:20:58.300 --> 00:21:00.385
That was an easier way to come and go.

286
00:21:02.513 --> 00:21:04.306
What? I'm hot.

287
00:21:04.389 --> 00:21:05.724
Yeah. and crazy.

288
00:21:07.518 --> 00:21:10.938
Yeah. well. takes one to know one.

289
00:21:18.862 --> 00:21:20.155
[dramatic. tense music playing]

290
00:21:20.239 --> 00:21:23.700
[both grunting. straining]

291
00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:28.163
[both panting]

292
00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:34.127
[panting]

293
00:21:38.090 --> 00:21:41.969
[both moaning. panting]

294
00:22:00.028 --> 00:22:01.947
[breathes shakily]

295
00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:03.866
Did Max make you do all of it?

296
00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:07.160
[sighs]

297
00:22:14.251 --> 00:22:15.252
He...

298
00:22:16.920 --> 00:22:18.797
He told me to break into your house

299
00:22:18.881 --> 00:22:20.007
and to...

300
00:22:20.841 --> 00:22:22.759
spike the tea with acid

301
00:22:22.843 --> 00:22:25.220
and to seduce your brother

302
00:22:25.971 --> 00:22:27.806
and make him bite off his own toe.

303
00:22:34.980 --> 00:22:37.983
But he didn't tell me to hook up with you.
I just wanted to.

304
00:22:43.864 --> 00:22:45.949
What does he want you to do now?

305
00:22:49.286 --> 00:22:50.954
He wants me to kill you.

306
00:22:53.415 --> 00:22:56.710
And he's not gonna stop
until he destroys your whole family.

307
00:22:57.920 --> 00:23:00.297
Yeah. well. he can't get to you in here.

308
00:23:02.424 --> 00:23:05.010
My mom can help. We can go to the cops.

309
00:23:05.594 --> 00:23:08.805
Yeah. I will not kill you.
but I'm definitely not turning on Max.

310
00:23:18.565 --> 00:23:20.817
[Crystal] Well.
I don't think anyone's here.

311
00:23:20.901 --> 00:23:24.363
You know. Brenda works down
at the bait shop sometimes.

312
00:23:24.446 --> 00:23:26.865
Uh. we could try to find her there.

313
00:23:28.242 --> 00:23:30.494
[eerie. mysterious music playing]

314
00:23:32.204 --> 00:23:33.455
Is that Amy's trailer?

315
00:23:35.040 --> 00:23:36.542
Where she shot herself.

316
00:23:41.380 --> 00:23:44.132
Wait! I don't think
we should go down there.

317
00:23:44.216 --> 00:23:45.259
It's a crime scene.

318
00:23:45.342 --> 00:23:47.511
It's fine.
I'm just gonna have a quick look.

319
00:23:49.179 --> 00:23:50.180
Well...

320
00:23:51.348 --> 00:23:53.392
[stammers] ...it doesn't feel right.

321
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:55.686
Oh. Wait.

322
00:23:55.769 --> 00:23:56.770
No. it's fine.

323
00:23:59.189 --> 00:24:00.566
Seal's already broke.

324
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:23.714
[dramatic sting plays]

325
00:24:23.797 --> 00:24:26.884
[eerie. mysterious music continues]

326
00:24:37.436 --> 00:24:40.063
[intriguing music playing]

327
00:24:56.163 --> 00:24:57.164
[Crystal clears throat]

328
00:25:06.757 --> 00:25:09.176
[Anna] That's you. With Amy.

329
00:25:10.761 --> 00:25:12.471
You and Amy Brancato were friends?

330
00:25:12.554 --> 00:25:16.433
[stammers] So. uh. we knew each other.

331
00:25:24.399 --> 00:25:25.567
Who's this?

332
00:25:27.903 --> 00:25:31.073
The boy. With the scar. in the photo?

333
00:25:33.575 --> 00:25:34.701
That one.

334
00:25:35.244 --> 00:25:36.828
We really shouldn't be here.

335
00:25:40.123 --> 00:25:42.668
[door opens. closes]

336
00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:31.758
[ominous music playing]

337
00:26:40.267 --> 00:26:41.268
[exhales sharply]

338
00:26:42.102 --> 00:26:45.105
[exhales shakily. panting]

339
00:26:52.779 --> 00:26:54.907
[phone buzzing]

340
00:26:54.990 --> 00:26:55.991
[gasps]

341
00:27:08.128 --> 00:27:09.463
[Max] <i>Hey.</i>

342
00:27:09.546 --> 00:27:10.923
<i>Did you get my gift?</i>

343
00:27:12.174 --> 00:27:13.300
Fuck you.

344
00:27:13.884 --> 00:27:14.885
Do it...

345
00:27:17.304 --> 00:27:18.972
and your children will be safe.

346
00:27:19.056 --> 00:27:20.807
<i>I'm not gonna kill myself.</i>

347
00:27:20.891 --> 00:27:22.518
- [sinister music playing]
- <i>Be brave. Tom.</i>

348
00:27:22.601 --> 00:27:23.894
You can't get to my kids.

349
00:27:23.977 --> 00:27:27.022
[sighs] <i>I mean.
Natalie is locked in with Nevaeh</i>

350
00:27:27.105 --> 00:27:33.862
and Zack is on the second floor
of the east wing.

351
00:27:34.905 --> 00:27:36.532
For now at least.

352
00:27:38.992 --> 00:27:40.077
That's bullshit.

353
00:27:40.160 --> 00:27:42.913
<i>Listen. I don't wanna
punish your children for what you did.</i>

354
00:27:43.664 --> 00:27:47.584
Your boy is like a son to me.

355
00:27:47.668 --> 00:27:52.256
[chuckles] And your girl...

356
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:57.094
Mmm. Well. our girl. [chuckles]

357
00:27:58.470 --> 00:28:00.013
Look... [sighs] ...enough.

358
00:28:00.097 --> 00:28:01.348
I'm giving you a...

359
00:28:02.307 --> 00:28:04.476
a chance at redemption.

360
00:28:05.269 --> 00:28:06.478
<i>Father to father.</i>

361
00:28:07.187 --> 00:28:09.106
Take back control. Tom.

362
00:28:09.189 --> 00:28:10.941
Save Zack and Natalie.

363
00:28:12.234 --> 00:28:14.069
Isn't it what your brother would do?

364
00:28:14.152 --> 00:28:16.446
[chilling music playing]

365
00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:21.994
[distorted screeching]

366
00:28:22.077 --> 00:28:25.497
Fuck you. Just...
[gasps] ...fuck you. Max! Fuck you!

367
00:28:25.581 --> 00:28:26.915
<i>I'll fucking kill you!</i>

368
00:28:26.999 --> 00:28:30.085
I'm gonna find you
and I'm gonna fucking murder you!

369
00:28:30.169 --> 00:28:31.170
Oh. God.

370
00:28:31.253 --> 00:28:32.838
Oh. oh. whatever.

371
00:28:42.264 --> 00:28:43.265
Max...

372
00:28:44.391 --> 00:28:47.311
he told me a story
about this girl named Lila

373
00:28:48.478 --> 00:28:50.606
that he seduced and abused...

374
00:28:51.732 --> 00:28:54.026
Crystal Delilah Cady.

375
00:28:55.694 --> 00:28:56.904
That's you. right? It was you?

376
00:29:00.908 --> 00:29:03.994
That boy in the picture. that's your son?

377
00:29:07.414 --> 00:29:08.415
With Max?

378
00:29:10.042 --> 00:29:11.835
Well. you don't know anything.

379
00:29:12.586 --> 00:29:14.838
What happened to him? Did he. uh--

380
00:29:14.922 --> 00:29:17.549
Well. I gave him away. What do you think?

381
00:29:18.383 --> 00:29:19.551
'Cause I'm a mess.

382
00:29:20.719 --> 00:29:22.471
[stammers] I don't wanna talk about it.

383
00:29:25.474 --> 00:29:27.809
You're not gonna win him back.

384
00:29:28.393 --> 00:29:30.229
You don't have anything he wants.

385
00:29:33.732 --> 00:29:35.025
Wait.

386
00:29:35.108 --> 00:29:36.693
Can I be honest with you?

387
00:29:39.571 --> 00:29:40.989
I've been here before.

388
00:29:41.615 --> 00:29:42.866
I broke in...

389
00:29:43.784 --> 00:29:48.330
because Amy. she told me that Max.

390
00:29:48.914 --> 00:29:51.375
he used to talk to her at night

391
00:29:51.458 --> 00:29:54.378
and she would fall asleep
listening to his voice.

392
00:29:54.461 --> 00:29:57.798
And so. I looked
and I found recordings of them.

393
00:29:57.881 --> 00:29:59.341
Wow.

394
00:29:59.424 --> 00:30:00.968
There are recordings?

395
00:30:01.051 --> 00:30:03.554
Yeah. all on a USB thing.

396
00:30:04.429 --> 00:30:05.514
Where are they?

397
00:30:05.597 --> 00:30:08.392
[exhales sharply]
They're back at the boat.

398
00:30:10.853 --> 00:30:12.729
[Noa] You should submit it
before the deadline.

399
00:30:12.813 --> 00:30:16.024
- so you'd better get your shit in order...
- Um. she's on the phone right now.

400
00:30:16.108 --> 00:30:18.277
[Noa] And that girl is not
spending the weekend

401
00:30:18.360 --> 00:30:19.653
- in youth detention.
- [Max] Hi. Noa.

402
00:30:21.196 --> 00:30:22.322
I'll call you back.

403
00:30:24.366 --> 00:30:25.367
Hope. leave us.

404
00:30:25.450 --> 00:30:28.078
Are you sure? I... [breathes heavily]

405
00:30:28.954 --> 00:30:29.955
How are you?

406
00:30:31.874 --> 00:30:32.958
What do you want. Max?

407
00:30:33.041 --> 00:30:34.543
Honestly. I want a friend.

408
00:30:34.626 --> 00:30:39.339
Because... [sighs] ...I thought Anna felt bad
about sending me to prison.

409
00:30:39.423 --> 00:30:40.424
And Tom too.

410
00:30:40.507 --> 00:30:42.968
But no. they-they tried to frame me.

411
00:30:43.051 --> 00:30:46.138
And you know what?
I can't understand that.

412
00:30:46.722 --> 00:30:48.849
So. you're here for sympathy?

413
00:30:48.932 --> 00:30:51.351
Y-Y-Y-Yeah. Kind of.

414
00:30:52.227 --> 00:30:54.021
Because I don't...

415
00:30:55.147 --> 00:30:58.525
[smacks lips] I try to think...
Like for example. do you think...

416
00:30:59.526 --> 00:31:00.944
No. not that. No.

417
00:31:01.028 --> 00:31:03.280
- What?
- No. do you think that...

418
00:31:03.363 --> 00:31:08.577
[sighs] ...maybe Anna didn't know
what Tom was doing?

419
00:31:09.745 --> 00:31:11.872
Because that will make me feel better.

420
00:31:12.706 --> 00:31:13.916
Do you think that's the case?

421
00:31:13.999 --> 00:31:16.084
[sighs] Let me guess.

422
00:31:16.752 --> 00:31:20.339
You wanna know where she is
so you could ask her?

423
00:31:20.422 --> 00:31:23.592
Yeah. That would be
the right thing to do. Noa. yeah.

424
00:31:25.010 --> 00:31:30.390
You think I'm so dumb
that I'll tell you where to find her?

425
00:31:32.434 --> 00:31:35.354
I guess I was dumb enough
to let you into our lives.

426
00:31:35.938 --> 00:31:37.773
so you could kill my friend Ray.

427
00:31:38.273 --> 00:31:39.650
torture my friend Anna.

428
00:31:40.943 --> 00:31:43.737
Both of which will be on me
until the day I die.

429
00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:46.323
but I see you now.

430
00:31:48.200 --> 00:31:50.202
I'm not scared of you.

431
00:31:51.119 --> 00:31:53.705
I've taken on the State of Georgia.

432
00:31:53.789 --> 00:31:55.999
I've taken on the US government.

433
00:31:56.083 --> 00:32:01.505
and I damn sure can take on
Max fucking Cady.

434
00:32:03.423 --> 00:32:04.424
I missed that.

435
00:32:04.925 --> 00:32:07.177
Do you have an address for Anna?

436
00:32:07.261 --> 00:32:09.263
[ominous music playing]

437
00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:20.816
Where the fuck is Anna?

438
00:32:28.323 --> 00:32:29.324
Noa?

439
00:32:30.534 --> 00:32:34.413
Where the fuck is Anna?

440
00:32:35.831 --> 00:32:37.833
[phone buzzing]

441
00:32:41.336 --> 00:32:43.964
Uh. actually. never mind.

442
00:32:44.506 --> 00:32:47.134
[chuckles] See you around.

443
00:32:47.217 --> 00:32:48.468
You look beautiful.

444
00:32:51.054 --> 00:32:52.055
Thank you.

445
00:32:55.684 --> 00:32:57.603
[line rings]

446
00:32:57.686 --> 00:32:59.188
[receptionist] <i>Oak Grove Psychiatric.</i>

447
00:32:59.271 --> 00:33:00.981
It's Tom Bowden. I'd like to speak with--

448
00:33:01.064 --> 00:33:03.609
[receptionist]
<i>Um. one moment. I'll get him.</i>

449
00:33:06.069 --> 00:33:07.779
[doctor] <i>Mr. Bowden? Uh. hello.</i>

450
00:33:07.863 --> 00:33:09.948
We. um. we've been trying
to reach you and your wife.

451
00:33:10.032 --> 00:33:11.992
There's been an incident with Zack.

452
00:33:13.702 --> 00:33:16.205
What incident?
Just let me speak to my son.

453
00:33:16.288 --> 00:33:19.750
Yeah. I-I don't know how it happened but.
somehow. he managed to get past security

454
00:33:19.833 --> 00:33:23.462
<i>and we haven't been able
to find him anywhere nearby</i>

455
00:33:23.545 --> 00:33:27.591
<i>so perhaps. uh. someone gave him a ride
or he had help...</i>

456
00:33:27.674 --> 00:33:29.468
- You-You fucking idiot.
- <i>Listen. if this is--</i>

457
00:33:29.551 --> 00:33:32.137
He's got my son! [exhales sharply]

458
00:33:34.014 --> 00:33:35.474
Jared. you gotta call me back.

459
00:33:36.183 --> 00:33:38.560
Uh. Zack's missing. I think Max has him.

460
00:33:38.644 --> 00:33:41.146
And you gotta let me know
if Natalie's safe. all right?

461
00:33:41.230 --> 00:33:43.482
Uh. call me back.
I've only got a little battery left.

462
00:33:43.565 --> 00:33:45.943
As soon as you get this. Noa.
whatever it takes.

463
00:33:46.026 --> 00:33:47.653
[Anna] <i>Please leave a message
after the tone.</i>

464
00:33:47.736 --> 00:33:49.446
[tone beeps]

465
00:33:49.530 --> 00:33:50.739
Hey. it's me.

466
00:33:52.991 --> 00:33:54.952
I don't know where you are. um.

467
00:33:56.203 --> 00:33:57.621
and I don't know where the kids are.

468
00:33:59.623 --> 00:34:00.624
I love you.

469
00:34:00.707 --> 00:34:02.709
[ominous music playing]

470
00:34:05.087 --> 00:34:06.088
[phone beeps]

471
00:34:09.842 --> 00:34:10.842
[grunts]

472
00:34:15.097 --> 00:34:16.098
[grunts]

473
00:34:22.187 --> 00:34:24.188
[suspenseful music playing]

474
00:34:31.905 --> 00:34:33.072
Your girlfriend got bailed out.

475
00:34:38.161 --> 00:34:40.038
[Nevaeh] No. No! No! No! No! No!

476
00:34:40.121 --> 00:34:41.164
- [door buzzes]
- Natalie.

477
00:34:42.958 --> 00:34:43.958
What did you do?

478
00:34:44.042 --> 00:34:46.043
- Wait. what did you do?
- [door buzzes]

479
00:34:46.128 --> 00:34:47.504
What did you do?

480
00:34:47.588 --> 00:34:49.755
Wait. wait. wait. wait!
Don't leave. don't leave.

481
00:34:49.840 --> 00:34:52.467
Don't leave. don't leave.
don't leave. Wait.

482
00:34:52.551 --> 00:34:54.428
Fuck you! Fuck you!

483
00:34:54.511 --> 00:34:57.598
- [cries] No.
- [door closes]

484
00:34:59.433 --> 00:35:01.435
[suspenseful music playing]

485
00:35:03.228 --> 00:35:05.522
[Anna] So where are these recordings?

486
00:35:07.357 --> 00:35:09.651
It's just right there. The...

487
00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:11.737
You lift the latch up.

488
00:35:13.155 --> 00:35:14.448
It's a little heavy. but...

489
00:35:15.782 --> 00:35:18.660
And then. yeah. That's it.

490
00:35:20.204 --> 00:35:22.080
And there's a few boxes.

491
00:35:22.164 --> 00:35:25.209
The-- I think the box down on the right.

492
00:35:28.754 --> 00:35:30.088
Why don't you show me?

493
00:35:30.172 --> 00:35:32.382
What. are you afraid of small spaces?

494
00:35:32.466 --> 00:35:33.800
- I know. Just...
- No.

495
00:35:34.593 --> 00:35:36.303
No. I just want you to show me.

496
00:35:41.600 --> 00:35:43.185
- Okay.
- [gun clicks]

497
00:35:43.727 --> 00:35:44.937
You looking for this?

498
00:35:45.812 --> 00:35:47.814
[suspenseful music continues]

499
00:35:55.781 --> 00:35:57.783
Why were you wearing Melissa's necklace?

500
00:35:59.910 --> 00:36:01.286
What necklace?

501
00:36:01.370 --> 00:36:02.371
Oh. come on.

502
00:36:03.247 --> 00:36:05.082
- I don't know--
- And I saw you wearing it.

503
00:36:07.292 --> 00:36:08.710
- [chuckles]
- What did you do?

504
00:36:08.794 --> 00:36:10.838
[chuckles] I don't know.

505
00:36:12.673 --> 00:36:13.882
Did you kill her?

506
00:36:15.008 --> 00:36:16.343
Did you kill Melissa?

507
00:36:18.303 --> 00:36:19.555
[inhales deeply]

508
00:36:20.222 --> 00:36:22.558
I really understand.

509
00:36:23.767 --> 00:36:24.893
I really do.

510
00:36:25.811 --> 00:36:27.688
I mean. he was so good to her.

511
00:36:30.023 --> 00:36:31.066
And you were just...

512
00:36:33.193 --> 00:36:34.194
trash.

513
00:36:39.366 --> 00:36:41.743
She didn't deserve that life.

514
00:36:44.830 --> 00:36:45.831
So what?

515
00:36:49.585 --> 00:36:50.961
Fuck.

516
00:36:51.044 --> 00:36:53.005
[inhales sharply]

517
00:36:53.088 --> 00:36:54.339
Get in the hold.

518
00:36:55.632 --> 00:36:57.634
[suspenseful music intensifies]

519
00:37:05.809 --> 00:37:07.394
[phone buzzes]

520
00:37:07.477 --> 00:37:09.897
Anna. Hey.

521
00:37:10.981 --> 00:37:12.983
Hello. Where are you?

522
00:37:14.568 --> 00:37:16.153
I know you didn't kill Melissa.

523
00:37:16.987 --> 00:37:18.822
[inhales sharply]
<i>You didn't kill your wife.</i>

524
00:37:18.906 --> 00:37:20.324
Yeah. that's right.

525
00:37:20.407 --> 00:37:22.701
Amy Brancato killed Melissa. yes.

526
00:37:23.702 --> 00:37:28.123
No. no. I know that you got Amy to confess
but not because you were guilty.

527
00:37:28.999 --> 00:37:30.000
Okay.

528
00:37:30.792 --> 00:37:33.837
So. who killed Melissa?

529
00:37:35.380 --> 00:37:36.381
<i>Crystal.</i>

530
00:37:39.009 --> 00:37:41.261
<i>No. Crystal was in an institution.</i>

531
00:37:41.345 --> 00:37:43.889
No. Crystal got a guard to let her out.

532
00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:47.184
I can prove it.

533
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:49.311
And I've got Crystal.

534
00:37:49.394 --> 00:37:51.146
<i>Look. Crystal was pregnant with your child</i>

535
00:37:51.230 --> 00:37:53.148
<i>and she was watching you
play house with Melissa.</i>

536
00:37:53.232 --> 00:37:54.233
<i>and she just snapped.</i>

537
00:37:54.316 --> 00:37:56.735
Wait. wait. wait. [chuckles]

538
00:37:57.361 --> 00:37:58.695
What did you just say?

539
00:37:58.779 --> 00:38:00.906
Crystal was carrying my child?

540
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:02.449
[Anna] <i>Yeah. your kid.</i>

541
00:38:03.033 --> 00:38:05.452
The one that she said
she gave up for adoption.

542
00:38:05.536 --> 00:38:07.871
I don't know what she told you.

543
00:38:09.164 --> 00:38:11.124
But Crystal had a son.

544
00:38:13.001 --> 00:38:16.630
<i>And he's out there somewhere
and you can probably find him.</i>

545
00:38:18.465 --> 00:38:22.261
<i>I'm gonna text you an address
of a public place and we'll talk.</i>

546
00:38:23.512 --> 00:38:25.556
Then you are gonna leave me alone.

547
00:38:27.349 --> 00:38:30.769
You hear me? You're gonna leave me
and my family alone.

548
00:38:32.312 --> 00:38:34.356
<i>We didn't do this to you.</i>

549
00:38:36.567 --> 00:38:38.902
Okay. Send the address.

550
00:38:55.919 --> 00:38:56.920
[chimes]

551
00:38:57.880 --> 00:38:59.882
[menacing music playing]

552
00:39:12.227 --> 00:39:14.229
[menacing music intensifies]

553
00:39:16.857 --> 00:39:19.610
Is that your big plan. huh?
Just turn me over to Max?

554
00:39:19.693 --> 00:39:20.986
You think that's gonna win you back?

555
00:39:21.069 --> 00:39:24.698
[Crystal] He wants you even more
than he wants me. you bitch!

556
00:39:24.781 --> 00:39:26.241
[Anna gasps. yelps]

557
00:39:27.534 --> 00:39:28.577
[Robert] Get going.

558
00:39:29.369 --> 00:39:31.079
What now. Crys? Huh?

559
00:39:31.163 --> 00:39:33.332
How many times I gotta
wipe your shit off of my boot?

560
00:39:33.415 --> 00:39:35.834
I have a plan! Put her in the hold.

561
00:39:35.918 --> 00:39:37.503
- [Anna] No. please.
- [Robert] Get down there.

562
00:39:37.586 --> 00:39:40.797
- Get her in here. You need to go.
- [Anna] Don't do this. We can talk.

563
00:39:41.673 --> 00:39:42.716
[Robert] Close it up. boy.

564
00:39:42.799 --> 00:39:45.719
[Robert. Crystal
shouting indistinctly. muffled]

565
00:39:51.350 --> 00:39:52.601
[Crystal] Get out of here!

566
00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:57.481
[Robert] What were you planning on doing
if we ain't showed up?

567
00:39:57.564 --> 00:39:59.775
What. you think you were gonna
bash her on the head?

568
00:40:02.945 --> 00:40:04.279
[Crystal] Just leave me alone.

569
00:40:14.998 --> 00:40:15.999
[phone beeps]

570
00:40:16.083 --> 00:40:18.085
[line ringing]

571
00:40:20.963 --> 00:40:22.089
Don't hurt my son.

572
00:40:23.715 --> 00:40:26.844
[Max] <i>Tom. Set yourself free.</i>

573
00:40:26.927 --> 00:40:27.928
[call ends]

574
00:40:29.721 --> 00:40:31.139
[phone chimes]

575
00:40:32.099 --> 00:40:34.101
[ominous music playing]

576
00:40:46.905 --> 00:40:48.073
[breathing heavily]

577
00:40:51.827 --> 00:40:52.911
[sniffs]

578
00:40:56.915 --> 00:40:59.126
[breathing heavily]

579
00:41:05.174 --> 00:41:06.175
[knocks on door]

580
00:41:06.258 --> 00:41:09.803
Hey! I just need some air.
I'm having trouble breathing down here.

581
00:41:09.887 --> 00:41:11.430
- Please?
- Ma'am? [gasps]

582
00:41:11.513 --> 00:41:14.141
Oh. fuck.

583
00:41:14.766 --> 00:41:16.518
[gasps. yelps]

584
00:41:18.103 --> 00:41:21.690
Look. whatever the Cadys have done
for you. it is not worth it.

585
00:41:21.773 --> 00:41:24.151
[gasping]

586
00:41:24.234 --> 00:41:27.070
You keep running your mouth like that
and watch what happens to you.

587
00:41:27.154 --> 00:41:28.405
- Luke...
- [Luke groaning]

588
00:41:28.488 --> 00:41:30.741
...you don't wanna spend
the rest of your life in prison. do you?

589
00:41:30.824 --> 00:41:34.328
It'll be much easier
if you just shut up. ma'am.

590
00:41:34.953 --> 00:41:38.165
Oh. my God. [panting]

591
00:41:43.629 --> 00:41:45.464
- Are you okay?
- [Luke groans]

592
00:41:45.547 --> 00:41:46.924
Yeah. Yeah. I'm good.

593
00:41:47.007 --> 00:41:49.676
I've seen that scar before.
In your baby photo.

594
00:41:51.053 --> 00:41:52.346
[scoffs]

595
00:41:52.429 --> 00:41:53.597
What?

596
00:41:53.680 --> 00:41:55.682
[chuckles. pants]

597
00:41:57.100 --> 00:41:58.727
Does Max know you're his son?

598
00:41:59.561 --> 00:42:00.979
- What?
- [Crystal] That's not true.

599
00:42:01.063 --> 00:42:03.023
- I'm Crystal's son. ma'am.
- That's right.

600
00:42:03.106 --> 00:42:04.399
You're a lying bitch.

601
00:42:04.483 --> 00:42:07.361
- Max Cady is your dad. Luke.
- [Robert] She's lying. Luke.

602
00:42:07.444 --> 00:42:08.695
[Crystal] You shut the fuck up. bitch.

603
00:42:08.779 --> 00:42:10.572
- [Robert] Talking nonsense. Goddamn it.
- Why would you say that?

604
00:42:10.656 --> 00:42:12.199
- Nonsense. I'm telling you.
- She's a lying little bitch.

605
00:42:12.282 --> 00:42:13.992
- But Max is my mama's brother?
- Yeah.

606
00:42:14.076 --> 00:42:16.537
- [Robert] Son. goddamn it.
- She's a lying. deceitful little bitch!

607
00:42:16.620 --> 00:42:17.454
Shut her up. Luke!

608
00:42:17.538 --> 00:42:19.248
Yeah. but what about my dad. Mama?

609
00:42:19.331 --> 00:42:21.917
Your dad is... [stutters]
...exactly who I said he was.

610
00:42:22.000 --> 00:42:24.211
- he's a zero. he left a long--
- She's lying.

611
00:42:24.294 --> 00:42:26.129
You can tell she's lying. right?
Look at her.

612
00:42:26.213 --> 00:42:28.549
Don't you let her talk to that.
she's saying lies to you!

613
00:42:28.632 --> 00:42:30.133
[Robert] It's like I told you. Crys.

614
00:42:30.217 --> 00:42:32.970
Sins of the daughter
visit the whole goddamn family!

615
00:42:33.053 --> 00:42:35.722
Hold on. you're working yourself up.
I can see it.

616
00:42:35.806 --> 00:42:37.474
You settle down. boy.
or you gonna get some crate time.

617
00:42:37.558 --> 00:42:40.519
Am I gonna get fucking crate time? Huh?
Fuck you and your fucking crate time.

618
00:42:40.602 --> 00:42:42.271
- Don't talk to your grandpa like that.
- Huh?

619
00:42:42.354 --> 00:42:44.231
Tell me. Mama.

620
00:42:44.314 --> 00:42:45.899
I love you.

621
00:42:45.983 --> 00:42:47.317
- Don't fucking...
- I would never hurt you.

622
00:42:47.401 --> 00:42:49.945
- [Luke] Don't fucking tell me that!
- No. I would never hurt you.

623
00:42:50.028 --> 00:42:52.614
- She's a stranger. I'm your mother.
- Tell me the truth.

624
00:42:52.698 --> 00:42:55.284
She can't tell you the truth. huh?
She's lying to herself.

625
00:42:56.076 --> 00:42:58.078
- Would you shut up?
- [gasps. grunts]

626
00:42:59.496 --> 00:43:00.706
- [exclaims]
- Oh. Ma.

627
00:43:01.248 --> 00:43:02.666
[Crystal] Shut up!

628
00:43:02.749 --> 00:43:04.626
[grunting]

629
00:43:04.710 --> 00:43:05.961
[grunts]

630
00:43:06.670 --> 00:43:08.213
[Luke] Fuck you. you fucker!

631
00:43:09.756 --> 00:43:12.134
I fucking hate you. I fucking hate you!

632
00:43:12.217 --> 00:43:14.678
- Fuck you. you fucker! [grunts]
- [Crystal] Oh. God. Stop it!

633
00:43:14.761 --> 00:43:16.471
- You're gonna kill him!
- Get the fuck off me!

634
00:43:16.555 --> 00:43:18.974
- You lied to me. you fuck!
- [Crystal] Stop it! [groans]

635
00:43:19.057 --> 00:43:21.518
- [Crystal] Don't!
- Why did you lie to me? What the fuck?

636
00:43:22.477 --> 00:43:24.980
[shouting indistinctly]

637
00:43:26.023 --> 00:43:31.153
Fuck you! Fuck you!
Why the fuck did you lie to me?

638
00:43:34.031 --> 00:43:35.449
[Crystal] Stop it. you're gonna kill him!

639
00:43:35.532 --> 00:43:36.783
[Luke] Get the fuck off of me!

640
00:43:39.745 --> 00:43:41.288
[Crystal] Luke. stop.
you're gonna kill him.

641
00:43:41.371 --> 00:43:43.749
- [breathing shakily]
- [Luke screams]

642
00:43:43.832 --> 00:43:46.251
- [Crystal] Calm down.
- [Luke] What the fuck am I doing here?

643
00:43:46.335 --> 00:43:49.838
I wanna fucking kill myself.
You're a bad mother!

644
00:43:50.464 --> 00:43:51.673
[Crystal] Calm down!

645
00:43:53.884 --> 00:43:55.886
[dramatic music playing]

646
00:43:56.305 --> 00:44:56.339
